from pyjake.sparkmodule import udf_month
from pyspark.sql.functions import split
from pyspark.sql.types import StringType
from pyspark.sql.types import IntegerType
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf

spdf1_month=spdf1.withColumn('month',udf_month(spdf1.date))
# spdf1_month.show()

def season_fun(month):
    if (3 <= month) and (month <=5) :
        return "spring"
    elif (6 <= month) and (month <=8) :
        return "summer"
    elif (9 <= month) and (month <=11) :
        return "fall"
    else :
        return "winter"
season_udf = udf(season_fun) 

def illum_fun(illum):
    grade=int(illum/10000)
    if (grade <=12):
        return grade
    else :
        return 13
illum_udf = udf(illum_fun, IntegerType()) 

spdf = spdf1_month.withColumn('season', season_udf(spdf1_month.month))
spdf = spdf.withColumn('illum_index', illum_udf(spdf.illum))
spdf.show()
